\par
"Call the police!" Roger croaked to the nearest cashier as he scrambled to his feet.\par
\par
Kim continued around the central island to confront the wizened Paul. Kim took in the leathered face and the tattooed arm and wondered about the man's personal hygiene.\par
\par
Like everyone else in the kitchen, Paul hadn't moved from the moment Kim had pounded the counter. Some of the burgers on the grill in front of him were smoking.\par
\par
