\par
"It's hard to believe," Tracy said. "I guess I've always just assumed that meat was safe."\par
\par
"It's a sorry situation," Kathleen said. "With tragic consequences.\par
\par
For a few moments, no one spoke.\par
\par
"How well we know," Tracy said, as if suddenly realizing this was no idle conversation. Her daughter was no abstraction. A fresh tear streaked down her cheek.\par
\par
"Well, that settles it," Kim said. He abruptly got to his feet.\par
\par
"Settles what?" Tracy managed. "Where are you going now?"\par
\par
"To Bartonville," Kim said. "I'm going to pay a quick visit to Mercer Meats."\par
\par
